    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Which of the following numbers are divisible by <m>2</m>?
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>34\,436, 78\,135, 23\,521, 56\,490</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                To identify if a number is divisible by <m>2</m>, 
                we check if its last digit (the digit in the ones place) is either <m>0</m> or an even number <m>(2, 4, 6, 8)</m>.
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>34\,436</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The last digit of <m>34\,43{\color{red}6}</m> is <m>6</m>, which is an even number.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Therefore, <m>34\,436</m> is divisible by <m>2.</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>78\,135</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The last digit of <m>78\,13{\color{red}5}</m> is <m>5</m>, which is an odd number.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Therefore, <m>78\,135</m> is not divisible by <m>2.</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>23\,521</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The last digit of <m>23\,52{\color{red}1}</m> is <m>1</m>, which is an odd number.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Therefore, <m>23\,521</m> is not divisible by <m>2.</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>56\,490</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The last digit of <m>56\,49{\color{red}0}</m> is <m>0</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Therefore, <m>56\,490</m> is divisible by <m>2.</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                Hence, <m>34\,436, 56\,490</m> are divisible by <m>2</m>. 
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example> 
